Permutations are ordered Combinations
Combination Locks should be called Permutation Locks

Permutations (order matters): 2 types

    1. Repetition allowed - strings
        
        n items means n choices each time.
        choosing r of n means

        P(n,r) = n^r

    2. Repetition allowed - distinguishable objects
        
        n items, with r distinguishable objects,
        where n1 + n2 + ... + nr = n

        P(n,r) = n! / (n1! * n2! * ... * nr!)

        
    3. No repetition

        n items, reducing choice by 1 each time.
        n x (n-1) x (n-2) ...

        n items, select r

        P(n,r) = n! / (n-r)!

        Note: for all n items: n!


Combinations (order does not matter): 2 types

    1. No repetition

        reduce permutation formula be eliminating
        various orders of same objects:

        C(n,r) = n! / [r!(n-r)!]    Binomial Coefficient

    2. Repetition allowed


        C(n,r) = (n+r-1)! / [r!(n-1)!]


        Also the solution to the number of integer solutions
        to equation:

            x1 + x2 + ... + xn = r

Subsets: selection of elements from n items
    
    2^n subsets from n items


Recurrence Relations & Induction (recursion = induction!)


